#Check up

### Reception
- How can I help?
- Are you here for an appointment?
- What’s your name, please?
- Date of birth?
- Let me pull up your information.
- I’ll check you in.
- Hi, I have an appointment for a general check-up. / Hi, I’m here for a general check-up.



### Tests
- blood test
- urine test
- blood pressure
- routine tests


I have an appointment for a general check-up.
Your appointment is scheduled for 10:30 a.m. with Dr Harris.
Please have a seat in the waiting area.
The nurse will call your name shortly.
I need to take your vital signs.
I will check your blood pressure first.
Please stand straight so I can measure your height.
Please step on the scale.
Your blood pressure looks normal.
Everything looks good.
You are all set.
How are you feeling today?
Do you have any concerns you would like to discuss?
I have been feeling tired lately.
I think it is because I have been working long hours.
I have been going to bed late recently.
Do you experience any headaches or chest pain?
Do you have any allergies?
I will listen to your heart and lungs.
Please take a deep breath.
Everything sounds normal.
Do you exercise regularly?
I sit at my computer most of the day.
Sitting for long periods can cause fatigue.
Try to stand up and move around every hour.
Even a short stretch can help.
Overall, your health looks good.
Try to get at least seven hours of sleep each night.
Drink more water during the day.
